(20413, 'tramadol', 'N/A', 'moderate', '7.1 Serotonergic Drugs Based on the mechanism of action of SNRIs and SSRIs including escitalopram, and the potential for serotonin syndrome, caution is advised when escitalopram is coadministered with other drugs that may affect the serotonergic neurotransmitter systems, such as triptans, linezolid (an antibiotic which is a reversible non-selective MAOI), lithium, tramadol, or St.', 'DailyMed'),
(20413, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Concomitant use with SSRIs, SNRIs or Tryptophan is not recommended (7.2). Use caution when concomitant use with drugs that affect Hemostasis (NSAIDs, Aspirin, Warfarin) (7.6). 7.1 Monoamine Oxidase Inhibitors (MAOIs) [see Dosage and Administration (2.5 and 2.6), Contraindications (4.1) and Warnings and Precautions (5.2)]. 7.2 Serotonergic Drugs [see Dosage and Administration (2.5 and 2.6), Contraindications (4.1) and Warnings and Precautions (5.2)]. 7.3 Triptans There have been rare postmarketing reports of serotonin syndrome with use of an SSRI and a triptan. If concomitant treatment of escitalopram with a triptan is clinically warranted, careful observation of the patient is advised, particularly during treatment initiation and dose increases [see Warnings and Precaut', 'DailyMed'),
