(20565, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'severe', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Abatacept: Increased risk of serious infection. (5.1, 5.11, 7.2) Anakinra: Increased risk of serious infection. (5.1, 5.7, 7.2) Live vaccines: Avoid use with HUMIRA. (5.10, 7.3) 7.1 Methotrexate HUMIRA has been studied in rheumatoid arthritis (RA) patients taking concomitant methotrexate (MTX). Although MTX reduced the apparent adalimumab clearance, the data do not suggest the need for dose adjustment of either HUMIRA or MTX [see Clinical Pharmacology ( 12.3 ) ]. 7.2 Biological Products In clinical studies in patients with RA, an increased risk of serious infections has been observed with the combination of TNF blockers with anakinra or abatacept, with no added benefit; therefore, use of HUMIRA with abatacept or anakinra is not recommended in patients with RA [see Warni', 'DailyMed'),
