(8100, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'severe', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Other adrenergic drugs may potentiate effect. Use with caution. (5.3, 7.1) Xanthine derivatives, steroids, diuretics, or non-potassium sparing diuretics may potentiate hypokalemia or ECG changes. Use with caution. (5.7, 7.2, 7.3) MAO inhibitors, tricyclic antidepressants and drugs that prolong QTc interval may potentiate effect on the cardiovascular system. Use with extreme caution. (7.4) Beta-blockers may decrease effectiveness. Use with caution and only when medically necessary. (7.5) 7.1 Adrenergic Drugs If additional adrenergic drugs are to be administered by any route, they should be used with caution because the sympathetic effects of formoterol may be potentiated [see Warnings and Precautions (5.3, 5.5, 5.6, 5.7)]. 7.2 Xanthine Derivatives, Steroids, or Diuretics', 'DailyMed'),
