(23272, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'moderate', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Warfarin: Potential for decreased INR; monitor INR and adjust the dosage of warfarin, as needed, to maintain the target INR range. (7.2) CYP1A2 Substrates with Narrow Therapeutic Index (e.g., theophylline and tizanidine): Potential for increased exposure to CYP1A2 substrates; monitor drug concentrations of CYP1A2 substrates with narrow therapeutic index. (7.3) Inhibitors of Bile Salt Efflux Pump (e.g., cyclosporine): Avoid use. If concomitant use is necessary, monitor serum transaminases and bilirubin. (7.4) 7.1 Bile Acid Binding Resins Bile acid binding resins such as cholestyramine, colestipol, or colesevelam adsorb and reduce bile acid absorption and may reduce the absorption, systemic exposure, and efficacy of OCALIVA. If taking a bile acid binding resin, take OCALI', 'DailyMed'),
