(17682, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Oxytocic Agents: May augment the activity of oxytocic agents; concomitant use of intravenous oxytocic agents is contraindicated (4, 7.1). Remove vaginal insert at least 30 minutes before administering an oxytocic agent. (7.1) 7.1 Oxytocic Agents CERVIDIL is contraindicated in patients receiving intravenous oxytocic agents because CERVIDIL may augment the activity of oxytocic agents. A dosing interval of at least 30 minutes is recommended for the sequential use of an oxytocic agent following the removal of CERVIDIL.', 'DailyMed'),
