(29091, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Strong or moderate CYP3A inhibitors or P-gp inhibitors: Adjust dosage of VENCLEXTA. (2.6, 7.1) Strong or moderate CYP3A inducers: Avoid co-administration. (7.1) P-gp substrates: Take at least 6 hours before VENCLEXTA. (7.2) 7.1 Effects of Other Drugs on VENCLEXTA Strong or Moderate CYP3A Inhibitors or P-gp Inhibitors Concomitant use with a strong or moderate CYP3A inhibitor or a P-gp inhibitor increases venetoclax Cmax and AUC0-INF [see Clinical Pharmacology ( 12.3 )], which may increase VENCLEXTA toxicities, including the risk of TLS [see Warnings and Precautions ( 5.1 )]. Concomitant use with a strong CYP3A inhibitor at initiation and during the ramp-up phase in patients with CLL/SLL is contraindicated [see Contraindications ( 4 )]. In patients with CLL/SLL taking a s', 'DailyMed'),
